1
00:00:10,583 --> 00:00:12,833
[BOY giggling]

2
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,625
[BOY]
You grave ruiner.

3
00:00:27,791 --> 00:00:29,583
Hey, there, Zack.

4
00:00:32,208 --> 00:00:33,375
Hey there, little shit.

5
00:00:34,791 --> 00:00:37,875
I went to so much trouble
making that grave for you.

6
00:00:37,958 --> 00:00:40,208
Why would you go
and wreck it like that?

7
00:00:40,291 --> 00:00:42,041
[laughs]

8
00:00:42,125 --> 00:00:43,666
If you really
went to so much trouble,

9
00:00:43,750 --> 00:00:45,875
then why does it
look like crap, kid?

10
00:00:45,958 --> 00:00:47,666
I was in a hurry.

11
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:50,458
But, hey, if it's as ugly
as you say,

12
00:00:50,541 --> 00:00:53,666
that means you'll be
right at home in it, won't you?

13
00:00:53,750 --> 00:00:56,708
Not if I put you
in a grave first, you damn brat!

14
00:00:58,458 --> 00:00:59,833
-[BOY scoffs]
-[ZACK grunts]

15
00:00:59,916 --> 00:01:02,666
My name's not brat
or little shit.

16
00:01:02,750 --> 00:01:04,833
It's Eddie, so use it, okay?


17
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,791
Shut up!

18
00:01:07,875 --> 00:01:10,250
Did you have to mess up
her grave, too?

19
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:12,125
Now I gotta fix it.

20
00:01:12,208 --> 00:01:13,208
[grunts]

21
00:01:14,250 --> 00:01:16,125
Ah. She's great.

22
00:01:16,208 --> 00:01:17,625
I fell in love at first sight.

23
00:01:17,708 --> 00:01:19,541
You what?

24
00:01:19,625 --> 00:01:21,916
Before now, all I did was
make graves for people

25
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,750
who had already passed on.

26
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:25,875
It was getting kinda boring.

27
00:01:25,958 --> 00:01:27,875
I like digging graves,

28
00:01:27,958 --> 00:01:31,166
but I don't have any feelings
about the people inside them.

29
00:01:31,250 --> 00:01:32,958
Where's the beauty
in that, right?

30
00:01:34,666 --> 00:01:38,208
So, I decided to create
the perfect grave for Rachel.

31
00:01:38,291 --> 00:01:40,125
I understand her.

32
00:01:40,208 --> 00:01:43,000
She and I are almost
the same age and everything.

33
00:01:43,083 --> 00:01:45,333
Loving a person
who can love you back...

34
00:01:47,208 --> 00:01:49,458
that must be way better
than one-sided feelings

35
00:01:49,541 --> 00:01:51,666
for a messy, decomposing corpse.

36
00:01:51,750 --> 00:01:52,916
[chuckles]

37
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:55,541
Of course,
if she'd rather it be messy,

38
00:01:55,625 --> 00:01:57,625
that'd be okay with me, too.

39
00:01:57,708 --> 00:02:00,666
Are you trying to get me
to hurl up my guts or somethin'?

40
00:02:00,750 --> 00:02:02,583
I have an eye
for what's beautiful

41
00:02:02,666 --> 00:02:04,291
and what's not.

42
00:02:04,375 --> 00:02:06,333
She'd go so well in here.

43
00:02:08,166 --> 00:02:10,333
That's why I'll be
the one to kill her.

44
00:03:43,666 --> 00:03:46,541
Shut it. You ain't that special!

45
00:03:46,625 --> 00:03:47,833
[grunts]

46
00:03:47,916 --> 00:03:49,291
-[EDDIE laughing]
-[grunts]

47
00:03:55,416 --> 00:03:56,541
[electricity buzzing]

48
00:03:56,625 --> 00:03:59,083
Come out and fight,
you little necrophiliac!

49
00:03:59,166 --> 00:04:01,375
♪

50
00:04:05,958 --> 00:04:07,000
[gasps]

51
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:10,333
[doorknob rattles]

52
00:04:17,458 --> 00:04:18,333
Huh?

53
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:21,500
RACHEL: I'm gonna need that.

54
00:04:25,791 --> 00:04:26,958
[torch switch clicks]

55
00:04:27,041 --> 00:04:28,833
♪

56
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:45,375
It's another letter.

57
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:54,750
This is exactly like
the previous ones.

58
00:04:54,833 --> 00:04:56,166
"There is nothing
to worry about.

59
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:57,750
You and I want the same thing."

60
00:05:01,625 --> 00:05:03,541
-[EDDIE giggles]
-[gasps]

61
00:05:03,625 --> 00:05:05,833
-Who's there?
-[EDDIE] Hello, Rachel.

62
00:05:05,916 --> 00:05:09,375
I'm going to grant your wish
for you, isn't that great?

63
00:05:09,458 --> 00:05:12,833
But there's something
I want from you.

64
00:05:12,916 --> 00:05:15,791
You have to entrust yourself
to me completely.

65
00:05:15,875 --> 00:05:18,583
Love's better when it goes
both ways, don't you think?

66
00:05:21,166 --> 00:05:22,291
Ugh.

67
00:05:22,375 --> 00:05:24,541
[EDDIE] I understand you
more than you know.

68
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:26,041
You want to die.

69
00:05:26,125 --> 00:05:27,375
So...

70
00:05:29,708 --> 00:05:31,583
just tell me "yes."

71
00:05:32,583 --> 00:05:33,750
♪

72
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:36,416
I'm glad we finally met.
My name's Eddie.

73
00:05:38,541 --> 00:05:40,000
You don't have to run.

74
00:05:41,458 --> 00:05:43,041
I won't try to kill you
out of the blue

75
00:05:43,125 --> 00:05:44,416
like those other guys.

76
00:05:45,583 --> 00:05:48,208
Zack is so sloppy
when he kills people.

77
00:05:48,291 --> 00:05:50,750
He doesn't even care
about making it look nice.

78
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:54,083
But don't worry.
I'm not like that at all.

79
00:05:55,166 --> 00:05:58,333
I know everything
that happened to you, Rachel.

80
00:05:58,416 --> 00:06:00,375
About your mom and dad.

81
00:06:00,458 --> 00:06:02,708
Your whole story.

82
00:06:02,791 --> 00:06:04,375
Do you really?

83
00:06:04,458 --> 00:06:06,791
Yep. So you're in good hands.

84
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:12,041
In that case, can you tell me
why I'm in here?

85
00:06:12,125 --> 00:06:14,125
-What, did you forget?
-Mm-hm.

86
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:17,750
That's okay, it's not important.

87
00:06:17,833 --> 00:06:18,666
[RACHEL]
But I want to--

88
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:20,083
[EDDIE]
The point is,

89
00:06:20,166 --> 00:06:22,500
I can give you
a totally painless death

90
00:06:22,583 --> 00:06:26,166
and you'll have the nicest grave
you've ever seen.

91
00:06:26,250 --> 00:06:28,250
I can make your wish
come true, Rachel.

92
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:29,791
[RACHEL]
Hmm.

93
00:06:29,875 --> 00:06:32,291
Hey, why aren't you
saying anything?

94
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:38,208
Come on, please? It's easy.

95
00:06:38,291 --> 00:06:40,708
You just have to say "yes."

96
00:06:40,791 --> 00:06:43,083
That runt's gonna pay.

97
00:06:43,166 --> 00:06:45,541
Get back in here! Right now!

98
00:06:46,625 --> 00:06:48,833
Damn it.
I guess he can't hear me.

99
00:06:50,833 --> 00:06:53,208
That little
corpse-lovin' weirdo.

100
00:06:53,291 --> 00:06:55,250
Does he think he can one-up me?

101
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:57,166
No way am I lettin' him
slaughter the bitch

102
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,625
before I get to.

103
00:06:58,708 --> 00:07:00,458
[gasps]
Hang on.

104
00:07:00,541 --> 00:07:03,291
She told me there was
a room inside and to the right.

105
00:07:03,375 --> 00:07:06,416
Ah, man, I gotta do
everything around here.

106
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:08,583
[EDDIE]
Why haven't you said "yes"?

107
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:11,666
I know. Say your wish out loud.

108
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:13,083
Maybe that'll help.

109
00:07:14,458 --> 00:07:15,625
[shudders]

110
00:07:16,791 --> 00:07:17,708
[sighs]

111
00:07:17,791 --> 00:07:19,375
I want to die.

112
00:07:19,458 --> 00:07:20,916
I know you do.

113
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,833
And I'll be the one to kill you.

114
00:07:22,916 --> 00:07:25,750
So just tell me "yes."

115
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:29,333
♪

116
00:07:29,416 --> 00:07:31,083
This is so annoying.

117
00:07:32,208 --> 00:07:34,333
Is it because of Zack?

118
00:07:34,416 --> 00:07:35,875
Ugh.

119
00:07:35,958 --> 00:07:37,583
Why are you with him, anyway?

120
00:07:39,291 --> 00:07:40,583
Because...

121
00:07:44,041 --> 00:07:46,500
he promised
that he was going to kill me.

122
00:07:46,583 --> 00:07:49,041
Is that all?

123
00:07:49,125 --> 00:07:51,250
Why not let me do it instead?

124
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:53,250
I'm sorry, you can't.

125
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:56,083
If I die then he won't have
a way out.

126
00:07:56,166 --> 00:07:59,083
Why should either of us
care about that?

127
00:07:59,166 --> 00:08:00,791
[EDDIE]
It would serve him right.

128
00:08:00,875 --> 00:08:02,208
-[RACHEL] But...
-[gasps]

129
00:08:04,541 --> 00:08:06,500
All right,
little Miss Horror Show!

130
00:08:06,583 --> 00:08:08,333
-You in there somewhere?
-[gasps]

131
00:08:09,666 --> 00:08:12,208
[EDDIE] Ugh. I hate
the sound of his voice.

132
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:13,666
Anyway, you pick.

133
00:08:13,750 --> 00:08:16,791
Do you want to be killed
by him or by me?

134
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:24,000
My sweet Rachel.

135
00:08:24,083 --> 00:08:27,416
I'll make sure
you rest in peace, and beauty.

136
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:30,000
♪

137
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:36,375
[gasps]

138
00:08:38,083 --> 00:08:40,208
You don't know a damn thing
about what looks good,

139
00:08:40,291 --> 00:08:41,583
you understand me, punk?

140
00:08:41,666 --> 00:08:42,750
If you did,
you wouldn't kill her

141
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:44,416
with that boring look
on her face.

142
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,375
What the hell is wrong with you?

143
00:08:46,458 --> 00:08:48,208
Would you please keep it down?

144
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:50,166
I'm trying to have
a conversation with Ra--

145
00:08:50,250 --> 00:08:51,750
-[ZACK] Shut up, coconut-head.
-[EDDIE gasps]

146
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:53,583
Hey, you! Weird little girl!

147
00:08:53,666 --> 00:08:55,125
You can hear me in there, right?

148
00:08:55,208 --> 00:08:58,166
-Who, me?
-[ZACK] Who else?!

149
00:08:58,250 --> 00:09:01,250
Don't think I'm gonna let you
run around here on your own.

150
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:04,375
Every sick puppy in this dump
wants to end your stupid life.

151
00:09:04,458 --> 00:09:05,666
But whatever happens,

152
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:07,875
I'm gonna do the honors,
like it or not.

153
00:09:10,208 --> 00:09:12,041
I swear to God I'll kill you.

154
00:09:12,125 --> 00:09:14,583
[shudders]

155
00:09:14,666 --> 00:09:17,333
[bell rings, fades]

156
00:09:17,416 --> 00:09:19,416
[RACHEL]
You swear to God?

157
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:21,666
That's right. You heard me.

158
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:23,375
So...

159
00:09:23,458 --> 00:09:26,250
don't you dare let
anybody else do it first.

160
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,875
[RACHEL]
Okay.

161
00:09:33,958 --> 00:09:36,625
Then you should hit this section
of the wall as hard as possible.

162
00:09:36,708 --> 00:09:37,958
[chuckles]

163
00:09:38,041 --> 00:09:39,333
Hell, yeah!

164
00:09:51,791 --> 00:09:52,750
How's that?

165
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,708
[EDDIE]
This isn't fair, Rachel.

166
00:09:56,791 --> 00:09:58,000
[ZACK groans]

167
00:10:00,625 --> 00:10:02,333
Where is that munchkin at?

168
00:10:02,416 --> 00:10:05,083
[EDDIE] There's no problem
with me killing you.

169
00:10:05,166 --> 00:10:06,208
What are you, touched?

170
00:10:06,291 --> 00:10:07,791
There's a shitload
of problems with it.

171
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:10,041
[EDDIE] But you'd do
such an ugly job.

172
00:10:10,125 --> 00:10:11,458
What's the difference?

173
00:10:11,541 --> 00:10:14,875
[EDDIE] Listen, you don't want
this jerk to kill you.

174
00:10:14,958 --> 00:10:17,208
He won't be neat or gentle.

175
00:10:17,291 --> 00:10:19,250
It'd be better to let me do it.

176
00:10:19,333 --> 00:10:21,750
I told you to quit your yappin'
and leave her be already

177
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:23,458
or you're gonna get cut!

178
00:10:23,541 --> 00:10:27,083
[EDDIE] Rachel, I'll be the one
to put you to rest.

179
00:10:27,166 --> 00:10:29,500
When you're ready,
I'll be waiting.

180
00:10:29,583 --> 00:10:30,500
[door creaks]

181
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:32,750
-[electricity buzzing]
-[scoffs]

182
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:33,833
Ugh!

183
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:35,625
You're dead meat anyway,
you know that?

184
00:10:35,708 --> 00:10:36,791
Even if I don't murder you,

185
00:10:36,875 --> 00:10:39,916
something'll kill you
before too long.

186
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,875
-True.
-Hey!

187
00:10:41,958 --> 00:10:43,458
Like I told you before,

188
00:10:43,541 --> 00:10:44,958
if you wanna die,

189
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:46,958
then you're gonna have to
make yourself useful somehow.

190
00:10:47,041 --> 00:10:48,916
You mean, if I can help you
get out of here,

191
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,750
then you guarantee
you'll kill me?

192
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:52,250
Yeah, seein' as how
that's exactly

193
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:53,500
what I just friggin' said.

194
00:10:56,583 --> 00:10:58,041
But it's different now.

195
00:10:58,125 --> 00:10:59,666
How?

196
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:03,250
"I Swear to God."
That is what you said, right?

197
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:05,000
To God.

198
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:06,208
Yeah, I'm sure of it.

199
00:11:06,291 --> 00:11:09,083
You swore to God
that you were gonna kill me.

200
00:11:09,166 --> 00:11:11,041
So now you have to.

201
00:11:11,125 --> 00:11:13,500
You can't go back on that.

202
00:11:13,583 --> 00:11:15,291
Once more.

203
00:11:15,375 --> 00:11:17,250
Please just say it
one more time.

204
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:20,083
I need to hear it.

205
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:24,083
[sighs]
There you go again.

206
00:11:25,791 --> 00:11:28,291
Listen, kid. I told you.

207
00:11:28,375 --> 00:11:30,708
I really hate liars, okay?!

208
00:11:34,875 --> 00:11:36,916
I understand.

209
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,541
Now that that's cleared up,

210
00:11:38,625 --> 00:11:40,583
I'll try to find a way
to be useful to you.

211
00:11:40,666 --> 00:11:41,791
[scoffs]

212
00:11:41,875 --> 00:11:44,291
Glad you got it
through your skull.

213
00:11:44,375 --> 00:11:46,666
So, what should we do?

214
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:49,625
Well, I did hear the sound
of a door opening earlier.

215
00:11:49,708 --> 00:11:50,875
We should head towards that.

216
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:54,875
That boy, Eddie,

217
00:11:54,958 --> 00:11:56,583
he said he would be waiting.

218
00:11:57,625 --> 00:12:00,291
Great. Sounds fun. Let's go.

219
00:12:01,666 --> 00:12:03,666
♪

220
00:12:08,833 --> 00:12:10,625
I'm starting
to smell dirt again.

221
00:12:10,708 --> 00:12:14,041
Don't tell me there's gonna be
more graves up ahead.

222
00:12:14,125 --> 00:12:15,750
-Probably.
-Great.

223
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:17,083
Well, do me a favor

224
00:12:17,166 --> 00:12:19,250
and don't go divin'
into the first one you see.

225
00:12:19,333 --> 00:12:20,958
I would never commit suicide.

226
00:12:21,041 --> 00:12:23,166
[ZACK]
Oh, yeah. You did mention that.

227
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:32,166
So, anyway, I don't think
I caught your name.

228
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:36,833
You got one, don't ya?

229
00:12:36,916 --> 00:12:38,833
I told you, Rachel Gardner.

230
00:12:38,916 --> 00:12:40,791
[scoffs]

231
00:12:40,875 --> 00:12:42,666
I guess I'm fine
with keepin' you alive

232
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:44,291
till I can get
some use out of you,

233
00:12:44,375 --> 00:12:45,375
but I gotta say,

234
00:12:45,458 --> 00:12:48,208
dealin' with a sad sack
like you...

235
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:49,958
is a pain in the ass.

236
00:12:51,291 --> 00:12:53,791
So, we meet again.

237
00:12:53,875 --> 00:12:54,833
♪

238
00:13:00,791 --> 00:13:04,166
Is there any way I can ever be
good enough for you, Rachel?

239
00:13:06,916 --> 00:13:10,291
You have no idea
what a scumbag this guy is.

240
00:13:10,375 --> 00:13:12,833
He's got no sense
of beauty at all.

241
00:13:12,916 --> 00:13:16,125
And he was just as worthless
before he came to this building.

242
00:13:17,791 --> 00:13:19,708
[RACHEL]
I read his profile.

243
00:13:19,791 --> 00:13:22,333
Then why would you
choose him over me?

244
00:13:22,416 --> 00:13:25,416
I can put you to rest
so much better than he can.

245
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:26,583
What?!

246
00:13:26,666 --> 00:13:28,708
Dead is dead,
you smug little bastard.

247
00:13:28,791 --> 00:13:29,958
I'm sorry, Eddie.

248
00:13:30,041 --> 00:13:31,916
He swore to God
that he'd kill me.

249
00:13:33,208 --> 00:13:35,250
And that's not something
you can take back.

250
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:39,583
Swearing to God, nothing means
more to me than that.

251
00:13:39,666 --> 00:13:42,750
What kind of God
do you believe in?

252
00:13:42,833 --> 00:13:44,416
I don't get it.

253
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:46,458
Why would your God want that?

254
00:13:49,416 --> 00:13:51,291
Doesn't sound like
any God I know.

255
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:54,958
That kind of freedom

256
00:13:55,041 --> 00:13:57,291
doesn't exist
in this place, Rachel.

257
00:13:57,375 --> 00:13:59,666
We don't get to
make choices like that.

258
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,041
The only thing we've been given
is the right to hunt down

259
00:14:04,125 --> 00:14:07,333
anyone who comes onto the floor
we're in charge of.

260
00:14:07,416 --> 00:14:09,291
We make them sleep forever.

261
00:14:10,541 --> 00:14:14,000
And I'm in charge of B-4.

262
00:14:18,166 --> 00:14:20,208
Well, I've made my decision.

263
00:14:20,291 --> 00:14:21,916
♪

264
00:14:24,166 --> 00:14:25,583
And, Eddie...

265
00:14:25,666 --> 00:14:27,125
[gasps]

266
00:14:27,208 --> 00:14:28,416
...it still isn't you.

267
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:30,166
Suck on that!

268
00:14:30,250 --> 00:14:32,000
Guess you're the loser, shorty.

269
00:14:32,083 --> 00:14:33,916
[EDDIE crying]

270
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,583
[voice breaking]
You can't do that.

271
00:14:35,666 --> 00:14:37,458
It's not your choice!

272
00:14:37,541 --> 00:14:38,708
[chuckles]
What was that?

273
00:14:38,791 --> 00:14:40,583
Can't hear you
over all this victory.

274
00:14:40,666 --> 00:14:42,916
It's not fair,
you don't get to decide!

275
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,583
[heavy breathing]

276
00:14:44,666 --> 00:14:45,750
[crying]

277
00:14:49,958 --> 00:14:54,291
Rachel, I wanted to preserve
your perfect beauty in death.

278
00:14:55,875 --> 00:14:57,083
But...

279
00:14:58,958 --> 00:15:01,083
at least you can rest now.

280
00:15:01,166 --> 00:15:03,833
A grave is really comfortable,
you know?

281
00:15:03,916 --> 00:15:07,125
All dark and cool and quiet.

282
00:15:07,208 --> 00:15:08,291
So...

283
00:15:09,583 --> 00:15:11,708
let me put you inside of one.

284
00:15:13,625 --> 00:15:14,708
[grunts]

285
00:15:15,708 --> 00:15:16,666
[ZACK grunts]

286
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:17,708
[EDDIE groans]

287
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:19,250
You don't deserve her.

288
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:21,416
You're just a violent brute!

289
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:24,125
You're trying to do
the same damn thing.

290
00:15:24,208 --> 00:15:26,291
Don't compare me to you.

291
00:15:26,375 --> 00:15:28,750
No matter how much bigger
and stronger you are than me,

292
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:31,041
you're so dumb you can't even
kill people right.

293
00:15:31,125 --> 00:15:33,416
You're stupid,
that's what makes you so angry.

294
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:35,291
You're the one
who's getting all worked up

295
00:15:35,375 --> 00:15:37,041
because you've you got
such a raging hard on

296
00:15:37,125 --> 00:15:38,000
for dead bodies.

297
00:15:38,083 --> 00:15:39,375
Now you're getting nasty.

298
00:15:39,458 --> 00:15:40,583
[laughs]
That's what your mom said.

299
00:15:40,666 --> 00:15:42,708
Just be quiet!

300
00:15:42,791 --> 00:15:45,416
All I want is you, Rachel.

301
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:46,666
Nothing else.

302
00:15:48,083 --> 00:15:50,250
I'll seal you up for eternity

303
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:53,125
under a lovely tombstone
with your name on it.

304
00:15:53,208 --> 00:15:54,625
Once I bash your head in.

305
00:15:54,708 --> 00:15:56,166
-[grunts]
-[EDDIE laughing]

306
00:15:58,541 --> 00:16:00,791
The hell's with these lights?

307
00:16:00,875 --> 00:16:02,250
Doesn't matter
how strong you are

308
00:16:02,333 --> 00:16:04,791
if you can't see
who you're fighting, does it?

309
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:07,750
I've had plenty of practice
digging graves

310
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:09,250
in the dead of night,

311
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:10,791
so I can see you just fine.

312
00:16:10,875 --> 00:16:11,958
[grunts]

313
00:16:12,041 --> 00:16:15,375
Nice try.
Takes more than that to hurt me!

314
00:16:15,458 --> 00:16:17,666
[EDDIE] How long can you keep up
that tough guy act?

315
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:19,000
[grunts]

316
00:16:19,083 --> 00:16:20,625
[EDDIE]
Whoops, almost had me.

317
00:16:20,708 --> 00:16:21,708
[grunts]

318
00:16:21,791 --> 00:16:25,250
Dammit. Show yourself,
you psycho!

319
00:16:25,333 --> 00:16:26,916
[EDDIE] Watch where you're
swinging that thing.

320
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,583
Shut up! Hey, you.

321
00:16:28,666 --> 00:16:29,666
Can I help?

322
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:31,416
Do somethin' about the lights.

323
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,083
I'm sure there's
a switch somewhere.

324
00:16:33,166 --> 00:16:34,833
There damn well better be one.

325
00:16:34,916 --> 00:16:36,541
But I can't see in the dark.

326
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:39,208
Which is why
we need the lights on, genius!

327
00:16:39,291 --> 00:16:40,833
'Kay. Be right back.

328
00:16:42,583 --> 00:16:43,750
Hey, Rachel, wait.

329
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:45,375
[gasps]

330
00:16:45,458 --> 00:16:49,125
[EDDIE] He can see?
But how's that possible?

331
00:16:49,208 --> 00:16:50,375
[grunts]

332
00:16:53,250 --> 00:16:56,250
Ah. He's just
running on instinct.

333
00:16:57,875 --> 00:16:59,458
[panting]

334
00:17:02,666 --> 00:17:04,041
-[EDDIE giggling]
-[gasps]

335
00:17:06,708 --> 00:17:08,208
[giggling continues]

336
00:17:10,083 --> 00:17:12,208
[footsteps approaching]

337
00:17:18,333 --> 00:17:20,291
[giggling continues]

338
00:17:20,375 --> 00:17:21,375
[gasps]

339
00:17:28,541 --> 00:17:29,583
[gasps]

340
00:17:37,416 --> 00:17:39,000
I designed it just for you.

341
00:17:39,083 --> 00:17:41,333
[groans]

342
00:17:41,416 --> 00:17:42,458
Rachel.

343
00:17:43,875 --> 00:17:47,541
I'll close you up in that coffin
so you can rest forever.

344
00:17:47,625 --> 00:17:50,083
And I'll remake your headstone
so that it's even prettier

345
00:17:50,166 --> 00:17:52,541
than before that idiot
destroyed it.

346
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:57,250
But first I need to kill you.

347
00:18:00,458 --> 00:18:02,166
[EDDIE gasps]

348
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:05,166
Wow, you look like an angel.

349
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:07,333
Now our love can be complete.

350
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:11,416
I'll make sure
your timeless beauty

351
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:13,333
never fades away.

352
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:14,500
-[gasps]
-[switch clicks]

353
00:18:14,583 --> 00:18:15,625
[EDDIE grunts]

354
00:18:19,250 --> 00:18:21,041
[groaning in pain]

355
00:18:21,125 --> 00:18:23,291
[voice breaking]
Rachel... please.

356
00:18:27,208 --> 00:18:30,083
Please, tell me why.

357
00:18:30,166 --> 00:18:32,916
Even after I built
this amazing grave for you.

358
00:18:35,375 --> 00:18:37,416
I'm the only person
who understands

359
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:39,416
what you truly desire.

360
00:18:41,083 --> 00:18:44,583
You hurt me so bad, Rachel. Why?

361
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:46,833
Eddie, I--

362
00:18:46,916 --> 00:18:48,791
-[ZACK] Sorry, little man.
-[gasps]

363
00:18:48,875 --> 00:18:50,958
But the lady shot you down!

364
00:18:51,041 --> 00:18:53,125
[groans]

365
00:18:53,208 --> 00:18:54,125
[chuckles]

366
00:18:54,208 --> 00:18:55,208
[laughs menacingly]

367
00:18:55,291 --> 00:18:56,416
[EDDIE screams]

368
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,208
[EDDIE choking]

369
00:19:01,291 --> 00:19:03,208
[coughing]

370
00:19:03,291 --> 00:19:05,916
[gasping]

371
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,083
[snickers]

372
00:19:10,541 --> 00:19:12,083
[EDDIE]
Oh, Rachel.

373
00:19:12,166 --> 00:19:13,291
[groaning]

374
00:19:13,375 --> 00:19:15,583
I wish I could've put
you in here.

375
00:19:15,666 --> 00:19:17,000
[gasping]

376
00:19:17,083 --> 00:19:19,666
I hope you can see
how much I love you.

377
00:19:20,958 --> 00:19:23,625
Hey, look at that,
it's a pretty good fit.

378
00:19:28,625 --> 00:19:30,666
[weak breathing]

379
00:19:30,750 --> 00:19:31,750
[sighs]

380
00:19:35,375 --> 00:19:36,750
Not bad.

381
00:19:36,833 --> 00:19:38,500
I never would've figured out
that he was usin' a remote

382
00:19:38,583 --> 00:19:40,041
to control the lights.

383
00:19:40,125 --> 00:19:42,291
The timing was too convenient
for it to be a coincidence.

384
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:45,333
A remote seemed like
the most likely answer.

385
00:19:45,416 --> 00:19:47,041
[gasps]

386
00:19:47,125 --> 00:19:50,041
♪

387
00:19:57,458 --> 00:19:58,666
It's pretty.

388
00:19:58,750 --> 00:19:59,791
Ugh!

389
00:19:59,875 --> 00:20:01,708
So, I hope you found
the "up" elevator

390
00:20:01,791 --> 00:20:03,083
while you were at it.

391
00:20:04,166 --> 00:20:05,166
Well, did ya?

392
00:20:06,875 --> 00:20:09,125
No, but maybe if I push
one of these buttons.

393
00:20:11,208 --> 00:20:12,875
-[rattling]
-[gasps]

394
00:20:26,291 --> 00:20:29,416
It was hidden back here
the whole time.

395
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:32,166
Nicely done, but don't let it
go to your head.

396
00:20:32,250 --> 00:20:33,666
[scoffs]

397
00:20:33,750 --> 00:20:35,625
Well, Ray, let's go.

398
00:20:35,708 --> 00:20:38,083
Hold on. Did you...

399
00:20:38,166 --> 00:20:40,750
Move your ass! We gotta split.

400
00:20:43,375 --> 00:20:44,333
'Kay.

401
00:20:44,416 --> 00:20:47,208
♪

402
00:21:05,750 --> 00:21:06,958
So, um...

403
00:21:07,041 --> 00:21:08,000
Yeah?

404
00:21:08,083 --> 00:21:10,041
Um, did I help out
enough, mister?

405
00:21:10,125 --> 00:21:12,708
I wish you'd quit
that "mister" and "sir" crap.

406
00:21:12,791 --> 00:21:14,708
You're givin' me
the friggin' creeps.

407
00:21:15,875 --> 00:21:17,833
Should I call you Isaac?

408
00:21:17,916 --> 00:21:18,833
Uh...

409
00:21:18,916 --> 00:21:21,125
Nah, I'd rather
you call me Zack.

410
00:21:22,791 --> 00:21:24,291
Got it.

411
00:21:24,375 --> 00:21:27,250
Anyway, was I
useful to you, Zack?

412
00:21:27,333 --> 00:21:28,708
Yeah, kinda.

413
00:21:28,791 --> 00:21:30,041
But just a little.

414
00:21:30,125 --> 00:21:33,041
Keep it up
on the next floor too, would ya?

415
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:35,583
Okay. I'll try.

416
00:21:35,666 --> 00:21:37,666
Anything I can do to help you.

417
00:21:37,750 --> 00:21:39,666
-However...
-What now?

418
00:21:42,166 --> 00:21:44,416
You can't forget
what you promised.

419
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:46,000
Once we get out of this place.

420
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:51,708
You swore to God
that you'd kill me.

421
00:21:51,791 --> 00:21:53,125
Jesus, Ray.

422
00:21:53,208 --> 00:21:55,541
You're starting to sound
like a broken record.

423
00:21:55,625 --> 00:21:58,000
[chuckles]
Don't worry, I know.

424
00:21:59,416 --> 00:22:00,416
♪

425
00:23:28,875 --> 00:23:30,250
[elevator bell dings]

426
00:23:32,625 --> 00:23:33,791
Hmm.

427
00:23:33,875 --> 00:23:36,416
Why the hell can't we go
all the way to the top?

428
00:23:36,500 --> 00:23:37,416
[grunts]

429
00:23:39,958 --> 00:23:42,041
Well, this is gonna suck.

430
00:23:42,125 --> 00:23:43,833
[whirring]

431
00:23:45,541 --> 00:23:47,541
♪

